  "_note": "Path prefixes containing '*' use glob-aware matching (fnmatch-style). Use '*/docs/dev/foo-' to match the prefix 'docs/dev/foo-' anywhere under any worktree. Use '/docs/dev/foo-' to anchor at any path that ends with '/docs/dev/foo-' boundary. Shared protected list is the SOLE catch-all for /.claude/ \u2014 DO NOT add broad '/.claude/' to denied prefixes; use only the explicit subdirs above so legitimate worktree artifact paths remain writable. spec-20260507-142952 AC-1: cp-state-*.json globs are documented here AND propagated into every subagent role's denied_write_path_prefixes; spec-check.py is the only legal writer. policy_version 2 (spec-20260508-221237 cycle 4 manual reorg, 2026-05-09): adds first-class roles timeline and transportation mirroring their .md tools: [Read, Bash, Skill] declaration, with denied_tools=[Write,Edit,MultiEdit,NotebookEdit] as defense-in-depth Feb-13-2026 incident lock. These two role table entries are the ONLY residue of spec-20260508-221237 in the global tool-policy; the ga''ode-maps allowlist enforcement was moved to project-local /root/travel-planner/.claude/policies/gaode_policy.json + hooks/pretool-gaode_policy.py per user directive. policy_version 3 (spec-20260519-211515 R7 reconciliation, 2026-05-20): broadened codex-detection invariant \u2014 added Skill to allowed_tools for 9 roles whose agents/*.md mention codex consultation (architect, cleanliness-inspector, pm, product-owner, prompt-inspector, spec, style-inspector, ui-specialist, user). ba gained docs/dev/acceptance-criteria- and docs/dev/retrospective-classification- write-prefixes; qa gained docs/dev/retrospective-classification-. Reconciliation closes item 7 of qa-output-retrospective-classification-20260519-175339.json. policy_version 4 (20260521-090100, 2026-05-23): adds */docs/codex/ to allowed_write_path_prefixes for 11 codex-consultation roles (ba, qa, pm, architect, product-owner, user, ui-specialist, spec, prompt-inspector, cleanliness-inspector, style-inspector). dev excluded — wildcard * already covers docs/codex/. Establishes docs/codex/<task_id>/<role>.txt as canonical codex output path; demotes /var/tmp/codex-outputs/ to fallback. policy_version 5 (20260524-122910, 2026-05-24, spec-20260518-225715 Cycle 3 Debt 8 / AC-08): adds */.claude/dev-registry/*/blast-radius-map.json to ba.allowed_write_path_prefixes so BA can author its per-task blast-radius-map for the dev pipeline (Phase 1 prediction). The existing */docs/dev/acceptance-criteria- prefix is preserved. dev/qa unaffected because they consume the map but the file is authored by ba.",
